d Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Duffus, Morayshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Duffus, Moray, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Strathearn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Strathearn in Perthshire. The placename means ‘the valley of the river Earn’, from Gaelic <i>srath</i> ‘valley’ + the river name Earn."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Helen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of the name (Greek <i>Hēlēnē</i>) borne in classical legend by a famous beauty, wife of Menelaus, whose seizure by the Trojan prince Paris sparked off the Trojan War. Her name is of uncertain origin; it may be connected with a word meaning ‘ray’ or ‘sunbeam’ compare Greek <i>hēlios</i> ‘sun’. It has sometimes been taken as connected with the Greek word meaning ‘Greek’, <i>Hellēn</i>, but this is doubtful. In the early Christian period the name was borne by the mother of the Emperor Constantine, who is now usually known by the Latin version of her name, <i>Helena</i>. She is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Helen De Strathearn was born in Kincardine, Perthshire, Scotland as the daughter of Malise Strathearn Earl of Strathearn and Egidia Agnes Comyn. She married Reginald le Cheyne 4th of Inverugie. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. She died after 1361, in her hometown."},"et":{"–after 1361":"–pärast 1361","1278–1329":"1278–1329","–1361":"–1361","1270–1345":"1270–1345","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1257–1313":"1257–1313","1244–1320":"1244–1320","25 March 1313":"25. märts 1313","Aft 1320":"pärast 1320"," 1340":"1340","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1325":"1325","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1257":"1257","1400":"1400","1278":"1278","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","about 1345":"umbes 1345","after 1361":"pärast 1361","1329":"1329","Kincardine, Perth, Scotland":"Kincardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Duffus, Morayshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Duffus, Moray, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–after 1361":"–1361 jälkeen","1278–1329":"1278–1329","–1361":"–1361","1270–1345":"1270–1345","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1257–1313":"1257–1313","1244–1320":"1244–1320","25 March 1313":"25. maaliskuuta 1313","Aft 1320":"1320 jälkeen"," 1340":"1340","1340":"1340","1361":"1361","1270":"1270","1325":"1325","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1257":"1257","1400":"1400","1278":"1278","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","about 1345":"noin 1345","after 1361":"1361 jälkeen","1329":"1329","Kincardine, Perth, Scotland":"Kincardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland","Duffus, Morayshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Duffus, Moray, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–after 1361":"–après 